Root — pnpm-workspace.yaml, tsconfig.base.json, wrangler.toml (default watchllm-api, env.orchestrator, env.chaos, shared D1/R2/KV, API producer queue, orchestrator consumer), doc copies PRODUCT.md, ARCHITECTURE.md, ENGINEERING_RULES.md, SIMULATION_SPEC.md, SDK_SPEC.md, MONETIZATION.md, .dev.vars.example.
Scripts (root package.json)
dev:web / dev:api — dev:api runs pnpm build:types then wrangler dev.
deploy:web — pnpm --filter @watchllm/web build only (no Cloudflare Next adapter yet; add @opennextjs/cloudflare or static export when you wire Pages).
deploy:workers — three wrangler deploy targets (default + orchestrator + chaos). Wrangler may warn about multiple envs; you can pass -e per target when you’re ready to deploy.
wrangler.toml uses REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_ID for D1 database_id and KV id as you specified.

Local secrets
Copy .dev.vars.example → .dev.vars in watchllm/ and set real values (file is gitignored). You need at least BETTER_AUTH_SECRET (long enough), GITHUB_CLIENT_ID, GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET, and APP_URL.

